review:
I've played some more of it & decided to change my opinion to negative - the points I was previously referring to as "a little irritating" now seem to really get on my nerves & bad for such a small project.

It's a very small colorful card game (against AI) with unknown rules (rather simple so you can figure them out soon while playing). It runs in a borderless static window 800x600, so what you see there on Steam screenshots is just someone's desktop wallpaper behind the game window in the center. It's being controlled from keyboard with just 3 buttons: left, right, enter. The program looks, works & sounds nicely - fonts, ornaments, sounds etc.

There are 'troops cards' with number value & 'specials' with global abilities with which you can influence the game board. You play strictly in turns with the AI opponent & the point is to overcome his numbers with each move - if you can't do it you lose instantly. When you feel you might run out of numbers soon, you start using magic (delete the last opponent's card on the table, change table cards between the players, repeat the opp's move etc.). The one who keeps more power on hand in the end wins.

Negatives:
1. a time gap between the start & the ability to move really irritates me when playing a little longer; also no way to skip the dealing cards animation;
2. no resolution changes or scaling - how to play on larger monitors, 3 inch close?
3. no tutorial or a little explanation at least;
4. unreasonable achievements like "win 100 times in a row" - lol it's hardly possible to win 10 times in a row with such a luck-based gameplay;
